>im trying to find the bumper with those guard thingys. i forget what 
>theyre called. but theyre the generic 60's bumpers. with the pipe
>things on top.

Usually called "over-riders".  Somtimes called "the plumber's special".
In German M-code lists they are usually Rammschutz, "ramming protection".

>And, has anyone ever made their rear fenders back to normal? [...]
>would i be replacing a whole panel or what?

Usually you make up a panel that is just a little bigger than the piece
they cut out and weld it to your Bus, then sand, fill, and paint.  Rex
Rogers has a good write-up with pictures at
http://www.type2guy.com/59/59body2.html .

Matt Roberds


